<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>404 Error - Page Not Found</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Poppins:wght@300;600&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        * {
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            box-sizing: border-box;
        }

        body {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            font-family: 'Poppins', sans-serif;
            background-color: #121212;
            color: #fff;
            text-align: center;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 600px;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 8rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            margin: 0;
            text-shadow: 4px 4px 10px rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.6);
            animation: flicker 1.5s infinite alternate;
        }

        @keyframes flicker {
            0% { opacity: 1; text-shadow: 4px 4px 10px rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.6); }
            100% { opacity: 0.7; text-shadow: 2px 2px 8px rgba(255, 0, 0, 0.3); }
        }

        h2 {
            font-size: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        p {
            font-size: 1rem;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            opacity: 0.8;
        }

        a {
            text-decoration: none;
            background: #e63946;
            color: white;
            padding: 12px 24px;
            font-size: 1rem;
            border-radius: 5px;
            transition: background 0.3s ease-in-out;
        }

        a:hover {
            background: #ff4d5b;
        }

    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="container">
        <h1>404</h1>
        <h2>Oops! Page Not Found</h2>
        <p>The page you are looking for might have been removed or is temporarily unavailable.</p>
        <a href="/">Go Back Home</a>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
